browser-action.description:
Navigate to an url.
Possible parameters are: - url (required): URL to visit. The URL should include scheme, for example "https://". - waitForNavigation.url (optional): Enables a wait for page navigation after this action has been executed. The URL being navigated to must match this pattern. - waitForNavigation.timeout (optional): Enables a wait for page navigation after this action has been executed. The navigation must occur within the specified timeout in milliseconds. - waitForNavigation.until (optional): Enables a wait for page navigation after this action has been executed. The navigation will be considered done when the specified state is reached. Allowed values are : LOAD, DOMCONTENTLOADED, NETWORKIDLE, COMMIT
